{{Redirect|第六天|第六天魔王波旬|天魔|神社|第六天神社}}
'''Takajizaiten''' (他化自在天, {{lang-sa-short|Para-nirmita-vaśa-vartin}}<ref>坪井俊映「[https://doi.org/10.4259/ibk.3.191 浄土経典における天について]」、『印度学仏教学研究』 3巻 1号、日本印度学仏教学会、1954年、p.192。</ref>) is the highest realm of the [[Three Realms|three realms]] in the [[Desire Realm]] (欲界) and the lowest layer of the [[Heaven (Buddhism)|heavenly realm]] (天道) within the [[Six Paths|six paths]] (六道), specifically the sixth heaven of the [[Six Heavens of Desire|six heavens of desire]] (六欲天). It is the dwelling place of the [[Māra|Dairokuten Maō Hajun]] (第六天魔王波旬, {{lang|sa|Pāpīyas}}), the lord of desire and great demon king of the Desire Realm.

The name "Takajizaiten" derives from the nature of this heaven, where its inhabitants find pleasure in the transformations created by others, freely converting these into their own enjoyment. The male and female celestial beings here achieve satisfaction merely by looking at one another. When desiring offspring, the celestial beings create children according to their desires, who are born directly onto their laps. The beings in this realm are said to have a height of three ri and a lifespan of 16,000 years. However, a single day and night in this realm is equivalent to 1,600 years in the human world.

As celestial beings, the inhabitants of Takajizaiten are often depicted holding bows.

