'''Takajizaiten''' (他化自在天, {{lang-sa-short|Para-nirmita-vaśa-vartin}}<ref>坪井俊映「[https://doi.org/10.4259/ibk.3.191 浄土経典における天について]」、『印度学仏教学研究』 3巻 1号、日本印度学仏教学会、1954th year 、p.192。</ref>) is the highest Rank in the {{ill|Three Realms|ja|三界|qq=draft|qq=draft}} within the {{ill|Desire Realm|ja|欲界|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and the lowest layer of the {{ill|Heaven (Buddhism)|ja|天 (仏教)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in the {{ill|Six Paths|ja|六道|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. It is the sixth heaven of the {{ill|Six Heavens of Desire|ja|六欲天|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and the residence of the {{ill|Demon King of the Sixth Heaven|ja|天魔|lt=Mara|qq=draft}}, specifically {{ill|Demon King of the Sixth Heaven|ja|天魔|1=Demon King of the Sixth Heaven|lt=Demon King of the Sixth Heaven|1=Demon King of the Sixth Heaven|qq=Dairokuten Maō|Dairokuten Maō Hajun=Dairokuten Maō Hajun|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ({{lang|sa|Pāpīyas}}), the great demon king and lord of the Desire Realm.

This heaven derives its name from the concept that its inhabitants derive pleasure freely by using the joys manifested by others. Male and female celestial beings in this realm are said to find satisfaction merely by gazing at one another. When desiring offspring, their wish manifests as a child that appears directly on their lap. The celestial beings are described as having a height of three ri and a lifespan of 16,000 years. However, a single day and night in this realm corresponds to 1,600 years in the human realm.

The celestial beings of Takajizaiten are often depicted holding bows.

